title: For Sale/Trade:  AR15 with extras and ammo
postcontent:
This rifle is anchored by an Aero Precision lower, complete with a Rock River Arms lower parts kit, milspec buffer tube and 6 position stock. It's also sporting a Phase 5 Extended Bolt Release (V2) and an Ergo grip.  There are a few other hidden gems in this setup as well.  While it has a milspec trigger, the contact surfaces have been mirror polished and greased to provide a very smooth surface for the moving components. It also has a reduced power hammer spring and a special grip screw that contains inside it, another set screw that allows the overall trigger take up to be reduced and the trigger pull drops to a very respectable 4-4.5 lbs. The lower also includes a set screw with a small nylon buffer to tighten the tolerances between the upper and lower, thus allowing fewer moving parts and overall a more accurate gun. The upper receiver has a heavy 16" barrel with target crown chambered in .223 Wylde (allows you to shoot 5.56x45 or .223 Remington).  The barrel is also free floated and the quad rail provides plenty of room for all of your accessories. A micro gas block is installed and is  necessary to squeeze between the large barrel and the handguard. A BCM Gunfighter charging handle aids in chambering and clearing rounds when a scope is installed.  The BCG is full auto rated as well.  Comes with a box of ammo as well. Thanks for looking.   

Rifle was fired 4 times to verify function.

I include easy to fill out Assignment and Affidavit of Trustee. Simply have your friend or family member fill one out and they can use the NFA item instantly! No waiting, no need to file with the Court. Then, they can resign as Trustee if you prefer to not keep them listed on your trust at ANY TIME!

This can be a complex process and I am here to help. Please feel free to contact me with any questions you may have. I specialize in Estate Planning and Probate Law and I am a serious gun-enthusiast! Let me put my knowledge and talents to work for you. That includes drafting the entire Trust with your specifics, answering your questions, and customizing each document to your needs.

I have never received a single call or email from a client that said the ATF rejected their NFA Trust or their Forms prepared by me. I will walk you through every step of the process and answer all your questions so that this unnecessarily complex process is easy and painless.

Did you know you can also put regular firearms and items into this Trust? By getting an NFA Trust, you can obtain Title II weapons/items along with properly establishing good Estate Planning for all your firearms.


What the Trust includes:

- The NFA Revocable Trust with a Schedule A (14 pages)
- Certification of Trust (7 pages, this is the version you send in to the BATF with the required Forms)
- Appointment of Trustee (1 Page)
- Trustee resignation (1 Page)

I look forward to helping you obtain your own NFA items and protecting your property while keeping your information and collection as private as possible.

Call anytime. title: For Sale:  Way to get guns for the prices they used to be
postcontent:
Slickguns.com is a basically a search engine for finding the best deals in guns. Ive used it to get my springfield xd mod 2 for under $450 (shipping, transfer, taxes, etc all included in less than $450 and I got all of the promos). It doesn't take away from the ma and pa stores too because you still need an FFL dealer to get it for you and most places charge $15 or so for it, so they still get something.
ALSO! I use ebates like the commercials show and its totally legit. You get a $10 bonus when you spend $25 or more (Just go sign up with this link so that I get a bonus too for referring http://www.ebates.com/rf.do?referrerid=UY54qsshKEwAKDTvnHYOQQ%3D%3D&eeid=28187) 
After you get signed up, search for a store and then click on it and it takes you to that stores website( I get ammo from basspro, stuff from Walmart, etc.). Spend your first $25 and usually within a week you will have a $10 check mailed to you or I think theyre also doing a $10 Walmart gift card, but not certain. You also accumulate cash back on all purchases, usually between 1-5%. The reason you get paid is simply because other stores pay them for bringing in buyers. No scam or anything. I am just passing out some tips I use to save some money, especially around the holidays. God bless and merry Christmas!
